KW  - Strategic competition
KW  - Spanish banking
AB  - This paper presents a theoretical analysis of strategic competition in retail banking when some of the firms show expense preference behavior. The literature on expense preference behavior by banking firms is fairly large, but to our knowledge, so far, the strategic interaction between profit maximizing banks and banks with expense preference behavior has not been investigated. The paper has also an empirical interest since it is motivated by the current situation in Spanish retail banking where commercial banks, profit maximizers, compete with savings banks, non profit maximizers.
